UNITED STATES ex rel. Fred FRAZER, Appellant, v. Daniel E. BREITENSTEIN, U. S. Marshal, Respondent. UNITED STATES ex rel. Frederick v. GRIESMAN v. SAME. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 17, 1926.) Nos. 260, 274. Costello, Cooney & Fearon, of Syracuse, N. Y. (George R. Fearon and David F. Costello, both of Syracuse, N. Y., and Herbert Pope and Frank F. Harkness, both of Chicago, Ill., of counsel), for appellant Frazer. William F. Woollard, of Albany, N. Y., and Herbert Pope and Frank E. Harkness, both of Chicago, Ill., for appellant Griesman. Oliver D. Burden, U. S. Atty., of Syracuse, N. Y., and William J. Donavan, Asst. Atty. Gen., opposed.

Before HOUGH, HAND, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Orders affirmed, upon the authority of United States ex rel. Hughes v. Gault, 46 S. Ct. 459, 70 L. Ed.-(May 3, 1926).
